---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BackToTop from '../components/BackToTop.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Consulting | Technical Anxiety"
  description="Post-migration Azure architecture consulting. Platform observability, governance, and design for organizations that shipped to cloud and are now living with the consequences."
>
  <Header />

  <!-- Hero - full width, matches homepage hero style -->
  <section class="consulting-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="consulting-hero-wrapper">
        <h1 class="consulting-title">Consulting</h1>
        <span class="consulting-subtitle">Post-migration architecture for Azure environments in production.</span>
        <p class="consulting-lead">
          You migrated to Azure. It works, mostly. But costs are climbing without a clear reason, 
          incidents surface from users before your alerts do, and the next expansion is exposing 
          cracks in a foundation that was never quite finished.
        </p>
        <p class="consulting-lead">
          That is the problem I solve. Not in theory. In production, across 100+ organizations, 
          over twenty years.
        </p>
        <div class="consulting-hero-buttons">
          <a href="#contact" class="button button-primary">Start a Conversation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="consulting-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Who This Is For -->
      <section class="consulting-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Who This Is For</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          This is not for organizations at the beginning of their cloud journey. It is for those 
          12 to 24 months post-migration who are realizing that getting to Azure and operating 
          Azure are two different problems.
        </p>
        <div class="signal-grid">
          <div class="signal-card">
            <p>You have monitoring but no confidence in what it is actually watching</p>
          </div>
          <div class="signal-card">
            <p>Costs are unpredictable and the tagging hygiene from the migration never got cleaned up</p>
          </div>
          <div class="signal-card">
            <p>Policy exists on paper, but the environment has drifted and nobody owns enforcement</p>
          </div>
          <div class="signal-card">
            <p>You are about to onboard another team or product and the platform is not ready to hold the weight</p>
          </div>
          <div class="signal-card">
            <p>The team that built it has moved on and institutional knowledge left with them</p>
          </div>
          <div class="signal-card">
            <p>You are being asked to scale something that was never designed to scale</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- How It Works -->
      <section class="consulting-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">How It Works</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          Every engagement starts in the same place: a clear assessment of what you actually have 
          before recommending what you should do. The path forward is chosen from evidence, not assumptions.
        </p>

        <div class="funnel">

          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <div class="funnel-step">
            <div class="funnel-step-header">
              <div class="step-number">01</div>
              <div class="step-meta">
                <h3 class="step-title">Discovery Call</h3>
                <span class="step-price">Free &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; 30 minutes</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="step-description">
              A direct conversation about your current environment, the problem you are trying to solve, 
              and whether this is the right engagement for it. This is mutual qualification. You are 
              deciding if I am the right fit. I am deciding if I can add real value to your situation.
            </p>
            <p class="step-description">
              No pitch. No proposal template. Just an honest conversation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="funnel-arrow">&#8595;</div>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <div class="funnel-step funnel-step--featured">
            <div class="funnel-step-header">
              <div class="step-number">02</div>
              <div class="step-meta">
                <h3 class="step-title">Platform Assessment</h3>
                <span class="step-price">$750 &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Fixed scope, written deliverable</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="step-description">
              A structured review of your current Azure environment covering operational posture, 
              governance state, observability coverage, and architecture integrity. Delivered as a 
              written report that includes current state, risk surface, and a prioritized path 
              forward naming which engagements apply and why.
            </p>
            <p class="step-description">
              The deliverable is yours. If you choose to act on it independently, you can. 
              If you want to continue, the Assessment becomes the foundation for everything that follows.
            </p>
            <div class="assessment-includes">
              <h4>The assessment covers:</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Monitoring coverage and alert reliability</li>
                <li>Policy enforcement and environment drift</li>
                <li>Cost visibility and tagging hygiene</li>
                <li>RBAC structure and ownership clarity</li>
                <li>Organizational accountability gaps</li>
                <li>Prioritized recommendations with rationale</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="funnel-arrow">&#8595;</div>

          <!-- Step 3: Three Paths -->
          <div class="paths-section">
            <div class="paths-header">
              <h3 class="paths-title">Engagement Paths</h3>
              <p class="paths-description">
                The Assessment identifies which of the following apply to your environment. 
                Each can be engaged individually or combined. All are available as standalone 
                fixed-scope projects or as part of the monthly retainer.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="paths-grid">

              <div class="path-card">
                <div class="path-header">
                  <h4 class="path-title">Platform Observability</h4>
                  <span class="path-price">From $2,000</span>
                </div>
                <p class="path-description">
                  For environments where monitoring exists but nobody trusts it. Alert noise has 
                  replaced signal. Dashboards are built but not acted on. Incidents arrive from 
                  users before they arrive from tools.
                </p>
                <div class="path-deliverables">
                  <h5>Deliverables include:</h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Observability design covering what to watch and why</li>
                    <li>Alert thresholds that reflect actual operational risk</li>
                    <li>Runbook triggers and escalation paths</li>
                    <li>Ownership assignments so signal produces action</li>
                    <li>Log Analytics and Azure Monitor rationalization</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <p class="path-note">
                  The technical fix without the organizational accountability structure produces 
                  better-looking dashboards nobody acts on. Both layers get addressed.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="path-card">
                <div class="path-header">
                  <h4 class="path-title">Governance &amp; Scale</h4>
                  <span class="path-price">From $2,000</span>
                </div>
                <p class="path-description">
                  For environments where policy exists on paper but enforcement is inconsistent, 
                  costs are climbing without clear attribution, and the environment no longer 
                  resembles the original design.
                </p>
                <div class="path-deliverables">
                  <h5>Deliverables include:</h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Governance framework with enforcement approach</li>
                    <li>Azure Policy definitions and remediation roadmap</li>
                    <li>Cost control structure and tagging standards</li>
                    <li>RBAC rationalization and ownership model</li>
                    <li>Organizational clarity on who enforces what</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <p class="path-note">
                  Governance that blocks teams creates shadow IT. The goal is a framework that 
                  enables speed by removing ambiguity, not one that adds friction.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="path-card">
                <div class="path-header">
                  <h4 class="path-title">Platform Design</h4>
                  <span class="path-price">From $2,500</span>
                </div>
                <p class="path-description">
                  For organizations planning a migration, a significant expansion, or a rebuild of 
                  a platform that was shipped fast the first time. The goal is architecture that 
                  does not create the operational debt the other two paths fix.
                </p>
                <div class="path-deliverables">
                  <h5>Deliverables include:</h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Reference architecture with decision rationale</li>
                    <li>Implementation roadmap with sequencing</li>
                    <li>Observability and governance baked into the design</li>
                    <li>Organizational readiness assessment</li>
                    <li>Platform decisions documented so they survive team changes</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <p class="path-note">
                  Platform decisions compound. A weak foundation does not just slow you down today. 
                  It limits what you can build on top of it for years.
                </p>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="funnel-arrow">&#8595;</div>

          <!-- Step 4: Retainer -->
          <div class="funnel-step funnel-step--retainer">
            <div class="funnel-step-header">
              <div class="step-number">04</div>
              <div class="step-meta">
                <h3 class="step-title">Monthly Retainer</h3>
                <span class="step-price">20 hours per month &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; $5,000/month</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="step-description">
              For organizations that need sustained architecture guidance, not a one-time fix. 
              The retainer covers both organizational advisory and hands-on technical deliverables. 
              Weekly touchpoints, async availability, and active architecture work within the monthly hours.
            </p>
            <p class="step-description">
              This is selective. I work with retainer clients where I can add real value over time, 
              not where I am filling hours. The Assessment and initial engagement determine fit 
              before the retainer conversation happens.
            </p>
            <div class="retainer-covers">
              <div class="retainer-column">
                <h4>Organizational</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Architecture decision support</li>
                  <li>Stakeholder communication guidance</li>
                  <li>Team structure and ownership review</li>
                  <li>Technology selection advisory</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="retainer-column">
                <h4>Technical</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Hands-on implementation work</li>
                  <li>Policy and governance deliverables</li>
                  <li>Observability design and configuration</li>
                  <li>Architecture documentation</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Background Strip -->
      <section class="background-strip">
        <p>
          Twenty years. Helpdesk to platform architecture. Healthcare, energy, finance, SaaS. 
          Built managed services from scratch as employee #2 at 10th Magnitude. Currently Senior 
          Product Architect at Rackspace. Over 100 Azure environments. The pattern recognition 
          that comes from that volume is what you are actually buying.
        </p>
        <a href="/resume/" class="btn-secondary">View Full Background</a>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact Form -->
      <section class="consulting-section" id="contact">
        <h2 class="section-title">Start a Conversation</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          Fill out what you can. The more context you provide, the more useful the Discovery Call 
          will be. If you are not sure how to answer something, skip it.
        </p>

        <form class="contact-form" id="consulting-form">
          <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="consulting-inquiry" />

          <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="name" class="form-label">Name <span class="required">*</span></label>
              <input type="text" id="name" name="name" class="form-input" required placeholder="Your name" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="email" class="form-label">Email <span class="required">*</span></label>
              <input type="email" id="email" name="email" class="form-input" required placeholder="your@email.com" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="company" class="form-label">Company</label>
              <input type="text" id="company" name="company" class="form-input" placeholder="Organization name" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="size" class="form-label">Company Size</label>
              <select id="size" name="size" class="form-input form-select">
                <option value="">Select range</option>
                <option value="1-50">1 to 50 employees</option>
                <option value="51-250">51 to 250 employees</option>
                <option value="251-1000">251 to 1,000 employees</option>
                <option value="1000+">1,000 or more employees</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group form-group--full">
            <label for="cloud-state" class="form-label">Current Cloud State</label>
            <select id="cloud-state" name="cloud-state" class="form-input form-select">
              <option value="">Select the closest description</option>
              <option value="planning">Planning a migration or major expansion</option>
              <option value="in-progress">Migration in progress</option>
              <option value="post-migration-early">Post-migration, less than 12 months in</option>
              <option value="post-migration-established">Post-migration, 12 to 24 months in</option>
              <option value="established-scaling">Established environment, trying to scale</option>
              <option value="established-fixing">Established environment, cleaning up technical debt</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group form-group--full">
            <label class="form-label">Areas of Interest</label>
            <div class="checkbox-group">
              <label class="checkbox-label">
                <input type="checkbox" name="interest" value="observability" class="checkbox-input" />
                <span>Platform Observability</span>
              </label>
              <label class="checkbox-label">
                <input type="checkbox" name="interest" value="governance" class="checkbox-input" />
                <span>Governance &amp; Scale</span>
              </label>
              <label class="checkbox-label">
                <input type="checkbox" name="interest" value="platform-design" class="checkbox-input" />
                <span>Platform Design</span>
              </label>
              <label class="checkbox-label">
                <input type="checkbox" name="interest" value="not-sure" class="checkbox-input" />
                <span>Not sure yet, need the assessment first</span>
              </label>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group form-group--full">
            <label for="problem" class="form-label">What are you trying to solve?</label>
            <textarea 
              id="problem" 
              name="problem" 
              class="form-input form-textarea" 
              rows="5"
              placeholder="Describe the problem in your own words. No need to frame it technically. What is actually going wrong, or what are you trying to build?"
            ></textarea>
          </div>

          <div class="form-submit">
            <button type="submit" class="btn-primary btn-submit" id="submit-btn">Request Discovery Call</button>
            <p class="form-note" id="form-status">I respond within two business days. Discovery calls are scheduled within one week.</p>
          </div>
        </form>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <BackToTop />
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const form = document.getElementById('consulting-form');
    const submitBtn = document.getElementById('submit-btn');
    const formStatus = document.getElementById('form-status');

    form?.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();

      submitBtn.disabled = true;
      submitBtn.textContent = 'Sending...';
      formStatus.textContent = '';
      formStatus.className = 'form-note';

      // Gather checkbox values
      const interests = Array.from(
        form.querySelectorAll('input[name="interest"]:checked')
      ).map(cb => cb.value);

      const payload = {
        name: form.querySelector('#name')?.value || '',
        email: form.querySelector('#email')?.value || '',
        company: form.querySelector('#company')?.value || '',
        size: form.querySelector('#size')?.value || '',
        cloudState: form.querySelector('#cloud-state')?.value || '',
        interests,
        problem: form.querySelector('#problem')?.value || ''
      };

      try {
        const res = await fetch('/api/contact', {
          method: 'POST',
          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
          body: JSON.stringify(payload)
        });

        if (!res.ok) {
          const err = await res.json().catch(() => ({}));
          throw new Error(err.error || err.detail || `Request failed (${res.status})`);
        }

        formStatus.textContent = 'Sent. I\'ll be in touch within two business days.';
        formStatus.className = 'form-note form-success';
        form.reset();
      } catch (err) {
        console.error('Form submission error:', err);
        formStatus.textContent = err.message || 'Something went wrong. Please try again or email directly.';
        formStatus.className = 'form-note form-error';
      } finally {
        submitBtn.disabled = false;
        submitBtn.textContent = 'Request Discovery Call';
      }
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .consulting-page {
    padding: 2rem 0 4rem;
  }

  /* Hero - matches homepage hero style */
  .consulting-hero {
    padding: 60px 0 80px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, 
      var(--bg-primary) 0%, 
      var(--bg-secondary) 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .consulting-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background-image: 
      radial-gradient(circle at 20% 50%, rgba(33, 150, 243, 0.03) 0%, transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(circle at 80% 80%, rgba(33, 150, 243, 0.03) 0%, transparent 50%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .consulting-hero-wrapper {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .consulting-title {
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .consulting-subtitle {
    display: block;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .consulting-lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 660px;
    margin: 0 auto 1.25rem;
  }

  .consulting-lead:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .consulting-hero-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  /* Buttons */
  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-color);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1rem;
    transition: opacity var(--transition-fast), transform var(--transition-fast);
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-color);
    transition: all var(--transition-fast);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-color);
    color: white;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .consulting-section {
    margin-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  /* Signal Grid */
  .signal-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .signal-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .signal-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .signal-card {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .signal-card p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  /* Funnel */
  .funnel {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .funnel-step {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .funnel-step--featured {
    border-color: var(--accent-color);
    border-width: 2px;
  }

  .funnel-step--retainer {
    border-color: var(--accent-color);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--bg-secondary) 0%, var(--bg-tertiary) 100%);
  }

  .funnel-step-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .step-number {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    opacity: 0.4;
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 3rem;
  }

  .step-meta {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .step-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .step-price {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .step-description {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .step-description:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .assessment-includes {
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .assessment-includes h4 {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .assessment-includes ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .assessment-includes ul {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .assessment-includes li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .assessment-includes li::before {
    content: '\2192';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent-color);
  }

  .funnel-arrow {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    opacity: 0.5;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
  }

  /* Paths */
  .paths-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .paths-header {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .paths-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .paths-description {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .paths-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .paths-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .path-card {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .path-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .path-title {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .path-price {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    white-space: nowrap;
